page.title: 06OUTSKIRTS OF MARLOW
page.content: This square contains woodland.The farmland belongs to Low Grounds farm which is part of a syndicate also including Hooks Farm. There is a public house called The Hare and Hounds which is about 600 years old. Housing along and off the Marlow-Henley Road and running through this area is large and luxurious.There are several school houses occupied by the Headmaster and some of the staff of Sir William Borlaise in Marlow. There area also a few brick and flint cottages typical of the area.
